    {
      "title": "Aorist / geniş zaman (-ir)",
      "level": "A2",
      "function": "State habits and general truths",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 6,
      "explanation": "The aorist covers habits, general truths, and offers: içmek → içerim (I drink [habitually]), kalkmak → kalkar (he gets up). Single-syllable stems mostly take -ar/-er; longer stems take -ir/-ır/-ur/-ür.",
      "culture_note": "The aorist is also the politeness tense: 'Bir çay alır mısınız?' (Would you take a tea?).",
      "references": [
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Turkish grammar",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_grammar"
        },
        {
          "title": "Wiktionary: -ir (Turkish)",
          "url": "https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/-ir#Turkish"
        }
      ],
      "drills": [
        {
          "sentence": "Her sabah kahve {{answer}}.",
          "answer": "içerim",
          "translation": "Every morning I drink coffee.",
          "hint": "iç + -er + -im",
          "display_order": 1
        },
        {
          "sentence": "O erken {{answer}}.",
          "answer": "kalkar",
          "translation": "He gets up early.",
          "hint": "kalk + -ar",
